      • serializeHuffmanTree

        public static byte[] serializeHuffmanTree(HuffmanTree tree,
                                          BitBlob compressedData)
        Serializes the huffman tree to a format that can be read back when decompressing. This can be saved to a file and read back. The serialization in sequenctial order: serialized pattern: HEADER: 4 bytes = how many nodes there are (integer) 1 bytes = what is the byte cutoff DATA: n amount of dynamic chunks dynamic chunk pattern: 1 bytes for uncompressed data, 4 bytes for the amount it occurs in the original data (integer)
        Parameters:
        tree - huffman tree to serialize.
        compressedData - the compressed data. Used for byte cutoff.
        Returns:
        serialized byte array for this tree.
